So, from modest beginnings, Churchill now had a substantial force of soldiers, and a larger and more impressive fleet than anyone had initially conceded. 

So his plan now was to used the fleet, led by the Queen Elizabeth, to bombard the Ottoman fortresses guarding the Dardanelles, and only then for the troops to go ashore. The QE, together with the warship Inflexible, would move in with smaller ships alongside, escorted by minesweepers who would ensure their safe passage.
